"I have a feeling you're not telling me everything. But just because I'm kind I'll let it drop" *She says thoughtfully*

*She sighs and looks down at the ground as she walks along. The sun seemed to sink rapidly, till it was just above the brink of the horizon. The fading rays cast an array of colours across the sky*

"Aaahh.. my favourite time of night" *She grins, her fur turned orange by the light* "Best time for fishing as well!"

"My horn mostly.  It serves more than a handy climbing tool.  It's also a
dagger and a partical beam launcher.  It's not much but it served me through
tough times."

~Should I tell her?~  He asked himself.  He was afraid of revealing his
dangerous but powerful attack.  He has come to the brink of off-line many
times because of it.  Pegasus decided to just let the conversation drop and
tell people only on a need-to-know basis.
